<HEADLINE>
FT  03 FEB 94 / Insurer to drop bar to union recognition
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR, Labour Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MSF, the white-collar technical union, has secured a new recognition and
representation agreement for its 500 members working for Zurich Insurance in
the UK.
This follows the union's five-month campaign against the Swiss-owned
company. Zurich de-recognised the union last January after acquiring
Municipal Mutual Insurance. Details of the deal will be announced today.
MSF believes it has regained partial recognition partly because of pressure
from 83 local authorities which protested to Zurich.
Adverse publicity is understood to have caused acute embarrassment to the
head office in Switzerland.
The new agreement gives MSF representatives seats on the company's
consultative staff council. Union officials will have the right to represent
members. There has not been a full restoration of the union's position in
the company.
Just over a week ago Mr Denis White, the company's chief executive in the
UK, made clear his dislike for having any trade unionism among its Zurich
employees.
The Transport Salaried Staffs' Association said yesterday that it gained
4,100 members last year.
</TEXT>
