FT  03 FEB 94 / World Trade News: French employers back WTO
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BUCHAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
France's Patronat employers' federation said yesterday it would watch
closely to see if the Uruguay Round agreement for a new World Trade
Organisation fulfilled the 'great hopes' for this body, David Buchan writes
from Paris.
France championed the WTO in the Uruguay Round negotiations as a means of
reining in the US tendency to retaliate unilaterally against what Washington
deemed unfair trade practices. Mr Francois de Laage de Meux, head of the
Patronat's international committee, said he did not expect the US to abandon
entirely the unilateral provisions of Section 301 in its trade laws. This,
he said, would not matter, provided - once the WTO came into force - the US
only used its 301 weapon against non-Gatt countries in non-Gatt trade areas.
