<DATELINE>
   BUCHAREST
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Romania's ruling Party of Social Democracy said yesterday it had agreed on a
coalition with the hardline Romanian National Unity party to include other
extreme nationalist and former Communist parties, writes Virginia Marsh from
Bucharest.
The two parties said they aimed to include the Socialist Labour party,
self-proclaimed heir to the Romanian Communist party, and the anti-Semitic,
