FT  02 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Ex-Lands seeks Pounds 20m to fund property
buy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Ex-Lands, the property and leisure company, yesterday announced a placing
and open offer to raise a net Pounds 19.85m for the acquisition of a
substantial property portfolio.
The group, whose largest shareholders are the Saatchi brothers, is
topurchase Londinium Investments for Pounds 16.5m, providing it with a
number of office and industrial properties with annual rental income of
Pounds 1.9m.
Ex-Landsis issuing 35.28m new shares at 36p, compared with yesterday's
closing price of42 1/2 p, and Pounds 7.05m of 7.5 per cent convertible loan
stock. The shares are beingoffered to existing shareholders on a 3-for-10
basis and Pounds 3 of loan stock for every 50 ordinary shares.
This is the company's second share issue in sixmonths, as management reacts
to what it describes as a highly favourable climate for property
acquisitions. In July last year, the company launched a Pounds 14.3m open
offer and placement to pay for several properties in southern England.
Londinium owns 13 industrial/office properties around London, with a gross
asset value of Pounds 12.5m. In addition, it has agreed to acquire several
properties inthe Great Western Trading Estate, Brentford, for Pounds 4.75m.
Ex-Lands will pay Pounds 16.5m for the combined assets, of which Pounds
10.4m will be utilised to pay off Londinium's existing debt.
Following the acquisition, Ex-Land's gross rental income will be increased
to Pounds 3.6m, based on current rental rates.
The company is also involved in a number of golf course projects in
continental Europe.
