<HEADLINE>
FT  02 FEB 94 / Letters to the Editor: Market fear more likely a phobia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Dr IVAN COHEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir,Richard Waters' article on the structure of the US stock market ('The
price ofa share in the cake', January 31) provided an interesting view on
the problemsarising as a result of market fragmentation.
However, I would suggest that 'a far-reaching fear. . .that if the volume of
share trading is divided among an increasing number of arenas, the
efficiency of the market will eventually be undermined' is more truly a
phobia.
Surely if shares in a given company are traded on several arenas then
arbitrage will occur to the extent that all arenas in toto will act as
efficiently as if they were a single market. After all, isn't this what
happens to a large degree with the markets for international currency?
Ivan K Cohen,
lecturer in finance,
The Management School,
Imperial College,
53 Prince's Gate,
Exhibition Road,
London SW7 2PG
</TEXT>
