FT  02 FEB 94 / Statistics standardised
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER NORMAN, Economics Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A revised system of national accounts (SNA) that sets new standards for
countries to monitor economies was unveiled yesterday, writes Peter Norman.
The system modifies the accounting framework used for economic and
statistical analysis since 1968.
It will be used by former communist countries that once monitored economies
using the 'material product' accounting system. The US will also use the
system.
