FT  01 FEB 94 / World Commodities Prices: Coffee and cocoa prices in late
dive - Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COFFEE and COCOA futures prices both took a dive at the London Commodity
Exchange yesterday afternoon but still were unable to arouse much interest
from buyers.
May delivery cocoa ended Pounds 11 down at Pounds 904 a tonne, while March
coffee lost Dollars 7 to Dollars 1,165 a tonne.
At the London Metal Exchange ZINC prices tumbled in after-hours 'kerb'
trading under largely technical liquidation prompted by a move below Dollars
1,010 a tonne for three months metal. The market ended at Dollars 1,002,
down Dollars 12 from Friday, but above a chart-support line near Dollars
995. News that an announcement on cutting European zinc producing capacity
could be made in February cut little ice with the market.
